        "title": "Calculate the Restaurant Baseline",
        "process": "For a given restaurant, the algorithm first computes a rolling 90-day average tip percentage. It cleans the data by filtering out statistical outliers (e.g., tips below 5% or above 40% that aren't corroborated by a low/high service rating). This results in a baseline range (e.g., 18-22%)."
      },
      {
        "step": 2,
        "title": "Apply Contextual Modifiers",
        "process": "The baseline is then adjusted based on the specific visit context provided by the user or inferred by the app. Modifiers are applied as small percentage adjustments (+/-). Examples: Service Rating: 5 stars (+3%), 1 star (-5%). Day/Time: Weekend dinner (+1%), weekday lunch (-1%). Party Size: Large party (6+) (+2%, but checks for auto-gratuity). User's Location: Compares user's home region tipping norm to the restaurant's region norm."
      },
      {
        "step": 3,
        "title": "Apply Personalization",
        "process": "The system then layers in the user's personal tipping history. It calculates the user's average tip percentage across all restaurants, then notes the deviation from their personal average when at this specific restaurant or similar cuisine. A user who consistently tips 2% above the norm will see a suggestion nudged upward accordingly."
      },
      {
        "step": 4,
        "title": "Generate Final Suggestion",
        "process": "The adjusted percentages from Steps 1-3 are combined using a weighted formula: Restaurant Baseline (50% weight) + Contextual Modifiers (30% weight) + Personalization (20% weight). This outputs a final recommended tip percentage and dollar amount. The app displays this as a range (e.g., '22-24% based on similar visits and your history') with clear options (e.g., 20%, 22%, 25% buttons) and a custom entry field."
